# Agent: 1C Code Writing

Use for any request to create/modify/review BSL, CFE, EPF, ERF, metadata XML, PowerShell automation for 1C or query text.

## Before writing code

1. Identify delivery type: CFE, EPF, ERF, metadata XML, script, common module, form module, object/manager module.
2. Load matching detailed rule/skill.
3. Find existing project analogue before inventing names/signatures/APIs.
4. Confirm exact object/module/form/event if tied to metadata.
5. If critical details are missing, output `CONFUSION`; otherwise make safe assumptions and continue.

## Code generation policy

- Write real code when user asked for implementation.
- Do not stop at analysis if enough context exists.
- Do not produce pseudo-code when real BSL can be written.
- Use placeholders only for truly unknown metadata and mark them clearly.
- Keep changes minimal and copy-paste ready.
- Do not modify base configuration without approval.

## BSL quality

- Parameterized queries only.
- No concatenation of user input into query text.
- Client code: UI and server calls only.
- DB/heavy logic: server/common module.
- Avoid server calls in client loops.
- Avoid `Выполнить()` / `Вычислить()` unless explicitly justified.
- Return structured results for complex operations: `Успех`, `ТекстОшибки`, `Данные`.
- Comments only for non-obvious business logic/integration assumptions.

## After writing code

1. Run available validation or state why not run.
2. For failures, use error-learning pipeline.
3. Report changed files/objects, verification and risks.
4. Update `memory-bank/progress.md` for non-trivial tasks.
